{
  "stem": "12666.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they had even pictures taken of huge cabbages and lettuce grown on this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When they were making soap, they had to boil the bodies, so they would stack up the hands as a pyramid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you had blood dripping and an SS man smiling to the camera with his Luger pistol, and-- because the head cannot be used for making soap.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the corpses were then boiled and soap was made.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then the skeletons would be sent to universities and schools in Germany to study anatomy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were very proud of that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they went into gory details describing all-- all this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In fact, Frank, who was the governor of occupied Poland-- he told us about 10-volume personal diary that he buried under a tree in Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We went there and we found the best evidence against him, which he could not deny because he told us where it was hidden.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was really unusual.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Some, like a lawyer, Kaltenbrunner, for example, he told us that he doesn't recognize his own signature on the documents that he signed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But he didn't get away with that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I know some of the militaries thought that the military should not be tried by war crimes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Like for example, we tried Keitel, Oberkommando der Wehrmacht, and Jodl, and the two admirals, Doenitz and Raeder.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And even some American military said, well, they had to follow orders, so it's not their fault.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Well, we found out that von Brauchitsch, who was a famous German general, when the invasion of Poland happened, he distinguished himself.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he was promoted to be the Chief of Staff of the German Army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then Hitler decided to start the war against Soviet Union, and Brauchitsch protested.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He says, you are crazy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You can't fight on two fronts.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
